    "Metadata": {
        "Id": "1f9d1c87-71e8-48bd-a2ae-422e57656d85",
        "Type": "usercreated",
        "Title": "Hackers Rool, Soldiers Drool",
        "Location": "LOCATION_COLORADO",
        "PublicId": "109048369427",
        "ScenePath": "assembly:/_PRO/Scenes/Missions/Colorado_2/_scene_bull.entity",
        "TileImage": "$($repository 10ed84d6-ee7e-4686-97c4-78dbb181ea1e).Image",
        "Description": "The hackers&apos; quaint little gaming spot used to be supplemented with their stash of literature - or rather, their comics. If you look there today you&apos;ll instead find the soldiers&apos; literature, with their tales of mockingbirds and metamorphosis. You might be able to see what the problem is here... As for the specifics of the contract, it is believed one of their comics prophesied this hit - something about a sniper bestowing wrath from the comfort of his own home. Then again, it&apos;s only a story.",
